Nicholas P Godejohn was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Nicholas P Godejohn was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Review hearing on July 29, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Nicholas P Godejohn in court, in custody, with Attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.   Lesli S Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called for extradition hearing.  Defendant waives extradition today.  Exradition papers are filed/signed.  Court signs waiver of extradition papers and warrant for committment.  Copies provided to all parties.  Defendant to be held in Waukesha County jail for 30 days (Missouri officials to pick up Defendant).  Review hearing scheduled for July 29, 2015 at 09:30 am.  Court revokes bail.
Defendant to have no contact with the co-actor. Not to leave the state of Wisconsin.

Defendant Nicholas P Godejohn in court, in custody, with attorney Eryn M Menden.  Attorney appears as friend of the court.   Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court sets bail in the amont of 1 million  Hearing scheduled for June 29, 2015 at 08:30 am.
